action.thought:
The issue is about supporting generic user-implemented mapping methods. Specifically, when a user writes a generic method like:

```csharp
private Optional<TTarget> MapOptional<TTarget, TSource>(Optional<TSource> source)
{
    return new Optional<TTarget> { Value = Map<TTarget>(source.Value) };
}
```

Mapperly should recognize this as a user-implemented mapping method and use it to map `Optional<User>` to `Optional<UserDto>`.

This is related to issue #357 (which is about generic mapping support) and discussed in #444.

Let me explore the codebase to understand:
1. How user-implemented mapping methods are currently discovered
2. How generic type parameters are handled in mapping resolution
3. What changes are needed to support this feature

